In one situation, a student received an assignment update in a class WhatsApp group. The message was short and not very clear, and it didn’t properly mention the deadline or how the assignment had to be submitted. Because of this, a few students got confused and either submitted it in the wrong format or missed the deadline. This ended up affecting their marks and caused a lot of stress.
This situation could have been handled better if the message was written more clearly. The person sending it should have included all the important details like the exact deadline, format, and instructions in a proper way. It would also have helped if they confirmed whether everyone understood. This shows how important clear communication is, especially online
